    h2 Events 
    p You can override the following functions in your code to adjust the default behavior.
    p 
        table.row-hovering
            tr 
                th Function 
                th Event 
                th Parameters 
            tr 
                td insertBOMDone(id) 
                td This function gets invoked after the BOM panel elements have been added to the page, before BOM data is being requested from PLM
                td id = id of the parent div element (i.e. bom)
            tr 
                td changeBOMViewDone(id, fields, bomData, flatBOMData) 
                td When BOM data has been retrieved and BOM rows have been added, this function will be invoked. This function also gets invoked when users select another BOM view in the given drop down (if enabled with parameter 'views'). flatBOMData will not be null only if flatBOM data is being requested as well (depends on given paramter).
                td 
                    ul 
                        li id = id of the parent div element (i.e. bom)
                        li fields = list of fields available in the selected BOM view 
                        li bomData = BOM data as provided by the REST API
                        li flatBOMData = Flat BOM data as provided by the REST API
            tr 
                td clickBOMItemDone(e, elemClicked) 
                td When users click the upload button, this function gets invoked. It is only available if 'upload' is set to true and will open the file browser to initiate the file upload process.
                td 
                    ul 
                        li e = click event object
                        li elemClicked = jQuery element of BOM row that got clicked
    h2 User Interactions 
